4.00	Sharabha	Sharabha	Sharabha (Sanskrit: , ) is a creature in Hindu mythology that is part lion and part bird. According to Sanskrit literature, Sharabha is an eight-legged beast, mightier than a lion and elephant and which can kill the lion. Sharabha, can clear a valley in one jump. In later literature, Sharabha is described as an eight-legged deer.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/ed/Munneswaram_Sharabha.jpg/250px-Munneswaram_Sharabha.jpg
